Description:
Rum Balls

1 packet Marie biscuits crushed
1 can sweetened and condensed milk
1 TBsp desiccate coconut
2 TBsp cocoa
1-3 drops rum essence ( optional)
Extra coconut

Mix all ingredients in a bowl except extra coconut with a big spoon. Scoop out about one teaspoon at a time and roll into ball in the palm of your hands, then roll in extra coconut, until completely covered. Refrigerate for 2 hours, before serving. Can be made up to one week in advanced if kept in air tight container. You can double this recipe.
In hot  weather you may have to refrigerate before rolling into balls.

Baked Christmas Ham

Leg of ham
Packet whole cloves 
Packet star anise
Ginger Glaze
1 cup ginger wine*
1/3 cup packed brown sugar
1/3 cup ginger marmalade 

Cut through skin about 10cm from shank in decorative pattern. Slip finger under widest part of skin and peel back skin and remove. This can be reserved to cover ham while storing. Make shallow cuts diagonally in opposite directions to make diamond shape in fat. Put ham in large baking dish and pour in one cup of water. Cover shank end with foil.  Brush half glaze over ham and put as many star anise over the surface that will fit. Keep them in place with the cloves. Bake in preheat 180C oven for 30 minutes (should be all golden and cooked after 30 mins.). Carefully brush over the remaining glaze and cover loosely with foil. Cook for 30-45 minutes more, depending on the size of your ham. Remove from oven and baking dish and let rest before carving.  You can serve this cold or hot. Reserve the juice in baking dish if desired, which can be served with meat on the side.

Ginger Glaze
Put all ingredients into a small sauce pan and simmer until marmalade and sugar dissolved and sauce thickens. This can be done one week in advanced. 

* If you can not find ginger wine you can replace with ginger beer.

Traditional Shortbread

250 gms butter melted
2 cups plain flour sifted
2 TBsp rice flour 
1/3 cup icing or castor sugar sifted

Preheat oven to 160C and grease a baking tray with butter, then set aside. Mix all ingredients in a bowl until combined. Make a ball with the ingredients, with your hands and move to baking tray. Squash down with your hands until it is about 5mm thick and smooth any cracks. Prick entire surface with fork and bake in oven until just golden. Remove from oven and slice with a knife into small rectangles while still hot. Serve when cold.

Grandmas Punch

2L Pineapple juice
1.25L Lemonade
1.5L Cranberry juice
2 cans 440 gms Pineapple pieces in juice
2 punets strawberries washed and chopped
1 bunch mint washed and chopped
1 Lime finely sliced
1 1/2 cups Vodka (optional)

Place all items in fridge over night except ice (leave this in freezer.)
Place all items in a large punch bowl and stir well. Add as much ice as desired (4-5 handfuls.)

Cherry Tomatoe Bake

4 cups cherry tomatoes halved
3 cloves garlic minced 
2 TBsp olive oil 
1/4 teaspoon Salt and Pepper
1/2 cup feta crumbled
1 bunch dill chopped

Preheat oven to 180C while preparing the ingredients. In shallow baking dish place all ingredients. Cook for 30-40 mins. When tomatoes have all collapsed remove from oven. Stir and sprinkle with additional dill if desired.  Serve with BBQ meat.

* different variety tomatoes can be used, I prefer 2 red and 1 yellow punnet

FMN POPCORN 

1/3 cup popcorn
1 TBsp butter (can use coconut oil for vegans)
1 TBsp canola oil 
1 TBsp brown sugar
Cinnamon sugar to taste
Microwave proof bowl with lid

Place butter and oil in microwave proof bowl and melt butter and oil in microwave until butter melted (about 20 seconds.) Mix in brown sugar while still hot and stir all until combined, then add pop corn. Stir to coat all the corn and spread out evenly in the base of the bowl so corn is only one corn kernel deep. Place lid on bowl and cook until most of corn popped. This will depend on your microwave and you may need to experiment to get the timing right. My microwave takes about 3 3/4 minutes (not all the corn will pop!) Remove from microwave with oven mitts and carefully turn inside down and give a good shake. If your lid does not allow you to do this then stir well and ensure to get the melted juices up from the bottom to help coat all the popcorn. Give a good generous shake of cinnamon sugar on top or just plain cinnamon if you don't have cinnamon sugar. Then put your feet up turn on the movie and enjoy!

Check out more popcorn recipes on The Yummy Life web site.

Cottage Pie
FODMAP

One amount of mashed spud
600 gms mince meat (lamb)
2-4 garlic cloves crushed
2 carrots grated
1/2 cup frozen peas defrosted or a zucchini grated
2 Tbsps tomatoe sauce
2 Tbsps Worcestershire sauce
1 Tbsp corn flour 
1-2 stock cubes 
Olive oil 
Salt and Pepper to taste

Preheat oven to 180 degrees. Heat olive oil in large fry pan and add garlic. Once golden add mince meat and cook until brown add all other ingredients except spud. Cook until reheated and sauce thickens. Place in a tray and spoon over mash spud. Cook for 30-40 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with side salad or lots of tomatoe sauce!

Lasagne

1 packet oven ready lasagna
Grated cheese
One quantity meat sauce*
One quantity white sauce^

Preheat oven to 180 degrees. In large lasagna dish spread out 2 1/2 cups meat sauce over the bottom, then sprinkle over 2-3 handfuls of cheese o we the meat sauce.  Put one full layer of lasagna sheets to cover the meat.  Keeping adding layers in this same manner, until you come close to the top. Once close to the top of the dish and your at the last layer, put the meat sauce on the lasagna sheet then pour over the white sauce using the back if the spoon to disperse the sauce so it covers the meat sauce completely.  Sprinkle over enough cheese to cover the top and cover with foil.  Cook for 45 minutes, then uncover and cook for a further 15 minutes.

Meat sauce
1kg good minced beef
1 bottle tomatoe sauce
1 can chopped tomatoes
4 tbsp tomato paste
2-3 bay leaves
1 large handful oregano
4-6 garlic cloves crushed
Salt and Pepper to taste ( About 1 teaspoon of each)
Olive oil 

Heat olive oil in large sauce pan, then add garlic and cook moderately low heat until golden brown.  Add mince meat and cook until brown.  Add all other ingredients and bring to the boil. Reduce to a simmer and cook until reduced to your desired consistency.  (While the meat sauce is reducing you can make the white sauce.).  You can also add some red wine if desired.

White sauce
125 gms butter
1/3 cup flour 
2 cups milk
Salt and Pepper
Freshly grated nutmeg

Melt butter on low heat in a small sauce pan and add flour. Stir to remove any lumps, add a small amount of milk and stir in until it thickens, constantly stirring. Keep adding milk in the same fashion in small amounts at a time until all the milk is used up. Some times you have to add a bit more milk. Add the Salt and Pepper to taste and grate the nutmeg in and stir. Use immediately!
